The paper deals with interpreting neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of flip points is a novel technique that can be applied to various types of neural networks, making it relevant to several sub-categories. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the development and analysis of machine learning algorithms, including neural networks. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it deals with the study of intelligent agents, which includes machine learning. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as neural networks are commonly used in image recognition tasks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with neural networks. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the interpretation of outputs from natural language processing models, which can be neural networks.
